  <summary>7/27/1987--Introduced.
Amends the Federal Aviation Act of 1958 to prohibit smoking on passenger-carrying aircraft if the flight is scheduled for two hours or less or seating is not assigned. Directs the Administrator of the Federal Aviation Administration to promulgate regulations to implement this Act.</summary>
